    <!--Initially, the ul was populated with several li items. We deleted all, *except one*  and wrapped that one li item in #each handlebar tags. In this manner, we iterate through the array of fruit and for each item in the array and its content, we create a new li item. 
    Here, the *this* keyword inserts the current item's value in the list.
    Next step in workshop:
    https://github.com/foundersandcoders/express-handlebars-workshop#rendering-individual-fruits-pages
    
    'Hints:

    Copy across the relevant HTML code to an hbs file.
    Change the ./src/controllers/singlefruit.js.
    In the previous example we passed an array as an object property. You can make as many key value pairs on the object as you want, and they don't have to be arrays.'
    -->

    <section class="main__container--full-width">
      <ul class="fruit__list" id="js-fruit-list">

         {{#each fruits}}

    <li class="fruit__item">
      <a class="fruit__link" href="/fruits/{{this}}"><div class="fruit__image" style="background-image: url(/images/fruits/{{this}}.jpg)"></div></a>
      <div class="fruit__info">
        <h2 class="fruit__name">{{this}}</h2>
        <svg class="fruit__fav-btn"><use id="js-fav-btn" xlink:href="#icon-heart"></use></svg>
      </div>
    </li>

    {{/each}}

      </ul>
    </section>

  </main>

   <script src="/js/fruit-fav.js"></script>


